{"id":20083,"date":"2024-01-26T09:34:00","date_gmt":"2024-01-26T04:04:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/?p=20083"},"modified":"2023-06-27T09:24:55","modified_gmt":"2023-06-27T03:54:55","slug":"how-to-grow-herbs-at-home","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/how-to-grow-herbs-at-home\/","title":{"rendered":"5 Useful Tips To Grow Your Own Home Herb Garden"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Growing your own kitchen herb garden is now an easy task. Here are 5 useful tips to help you get started!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>There are plenty of ways to grow herbs at home. Whether it&#8217;s a small <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/balcony-window-design-ideas\/\">balcony window<\/a> in your urban apartment or a lavish garden, growing your own herbs is a privileged access to organic greens. The fragrance of freshly chopped basil sprinkled generously over hot pasta plucked from your garden. Or the robust earthy flavour of curry leaves sizzling in a pan can fill up an entire room. Just about everything tastes manifold better with fresh herbs. And then there&#8217;s the joy of growing them at home, but like every baby, these, too, flourish with love and care.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are 5 useful tips on how to grow herbs at home that save you the extra bucks and effort of bargaining for free coriander.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Preparing The Pots For Your Home Herb Garden<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>To create a thriving home herb garden, you only need three essential things: soil, sunshine, and space. Herbs are among the easiest plants to cultivate, requiring only warm rays of sunshine to flourish. Popular herbs such as parsley, basil, and coriander can thrive in a sunny corner of your home, making them perfect for growing in a small kitchen herb garden. Start by finding a suitable spot in your balcony or <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/kitchen-window-designs\/\">kitchen window<\/a> to place small containers with your seedlings. Make sure the pots have small holes for easy drainage, and place a tray beneath to collect excess water, keeping your garden area insect-free. With just a little effort, you can grow herbs in your kitchen and have fresh, aromatic herbs at your fingertips for all your culinary needs.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/27091520\/vertical-home-herb-garden-with-pots.jpg\" alt=\"Vertical home herb garden with pots facilitating easy drainage\" class=\"wp-image-46586\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/27091520\/vertical-home-herb-garden-with-pots.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/27091520\/vertical-home-herb-garden-with-pots-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/27091520\/vertical-home-herb-garden-with-pots-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/27091520\/vertical-home-herb-garden-with-pots-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>A lovely vertical garden with an easy drainage system!\n<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Potting The Soil To Grow Herbs In the Kitchen<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Growing herbs at home has numerous benefits, but perhaps the most significant is enjoying fresh, organic produce free of harmful pesticides. To achieve this, adopting conscious and sustainable practices in your herb gardening routine is essential. Start by segregating wet and dry waste from your kitchen to create compost that can nourish your seedlings. Items like used tea leaves, eggshells, vegetable peels, and leftover green stalks that typically end up in the trash bin are excellent sources of nutrients for your herbs. Using a half-and-half ratio of garden soil and homemade compost, you can grow your herbs through the zero-waste method. Whether starting a kitchen herb garden or growing herbs for home use, embracing sustainable practices in your herb cultivation journey is a surefire way to reap healthy and environmentally-friendly benefits.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/27091513\/upside-down-ceiling-hung-home-herb-garden.jpg\" alt=\"Upside-down ceiling-hung home herb garden which embrace sustainable practices\" class=\"wp-image-46585\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/27091513\/upside-down-ceiling-hung-home-herb-garden.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/27091513\/upside-down-ceiling-hung-home-herb-garden-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/27091513\/upside-down-ceiling-hung-home-herb-garden-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/27091513\/upside-down-ceiling-hung-home-herb-garden-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>A unique upside-down ceiling-hung kitchen garden<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Simple Care Routine To Grow Herb Plants In Kitchen<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Growing herbs at home is a breeze, but it&#8217;s crucial to remember that each herb variety has unique care requirements. Simplify your herb gardening routine by grouping herbs that share similar needs. For instance, coriander leaves dry out quickly and prefer partially shaded areas with moist soil, while mint thrives on winter sunlight and only requires occasional watering. When watering your herbs, it&#8217;s essential to do so frequently but test the soil beforehand to avoid overwatering. You can easily check soil moisture levels by inserting your index finger deeply into the soil or monitoring the colour of the leaves &#8211; yellow leaves are a sign that your herbs are at risk of drying out and perishing. So, whether you&#8217;re starting a kitchen herb garden or growing herbs for home use, remember these tips for a thriving herb garden.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/27091506\/Kitchen-hub-garden-care-routine.jpg\" alt=\"Kitchen hub garden care routine for a thriving garden\" class=\"wp-image-46584\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/27091506\/Kitchen-hub-garden-care-routine.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/27091506\/Kitchen-hub-garden-care-routine-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/27091506\/Kitchen-hub-garden-care-routine-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/27091506\/Kitchen-hub-garden-care-routine-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>A kitchen garden that borders the island for a green vibe!\n<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Clipping And Pruning Technique For Herbs To Grow At Home<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>There are plenty of easy herbs to grow at home, from basil (tulsi) to India&#8217;s favourite curry leaves. Some of these herbs even contain medicinal properties and are extremely easy to care for. However, even young plants require regular trimming to help the stems grow fresh leaves. When you notice flowers blooming alongside your herbs, it&#8217;s a sign that they are not being pruned enough. To preserve the nutritional content of your herbs, avoid trimming more than one-third of the plant at a time.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/27091458\/home-herb-garden-clipping-techniques.jpg\" alt=\"Clipping and pruning techniques for home herb garden to preserve its nutritional content\" class=\"wp-image-46583\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/27091458\/home-herb-garden-clipping-techniques.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/27091458\/home-herb-garden-clipping-techniques-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/27091458\/home-herb-garden-clipping-techniques-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/27091458\/home-herb-garden-clipping-techniques-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>An open-shelf kitchen garden with all the essential greens\n<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Budget friendly home interior solutions that are functional and stylish!\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/19104424\/budget-friendly-home-interior-solutions-that-are-functional-and-stylish.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Harvesting Your Kitchen Herb Garden<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Many individuals are curious about growing hydroponic herbs at home, and it&#8217;s no surprise why. This method of herb cultivation is becoming increasingly popular, especially in metropolitan areas with limited space. It&#8217;s also a cost-effective alternative to traditional kitchen gardening, making it a practical choice for those who want to enjoy fresh herbs year-round. So, if you&#8217;re looking for herbs to grow at home, consider trying your hand at hydroponic herb harvesting!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Hydroponic gardening allows you to grow a range of herbs, among which basil, sage, oregano, thyme, parsley, chives, tarragon and cilantro are the most common. Use a container to hold water and nutrient mixture for your herb roots. An air pump will evenly distribute oxygen throughout the container, preventing your herbs from wilting.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/27091452\/kitchen-herb-garden-harvesting.jpg\" alt=\"Harvesting ceiling hung kitchen herb garden for bohemian lovers\" class=\"wp-image-46582\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/27091452\/kitchen-herb-garden-harvesting.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/27091452\/kitchen-herb-garden-harvesting-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/27091452\/kitchen-herb-garden-harvesting-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/27091452\/kitchen-herb-garden-harvesting-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Ceiling hung, macrame kitchen garden for bohemian lovers<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In conclusion, growing herbs at home can be a fun and rewarding experience. Whether you&#8217;re looking to add fresh flavours to your meals or simply enjoy the process of gardening, a kitchen herb garden or a home herb garden is a great place to start. With the right tools, knowledge, and a little patience, you can create a beautiful and bountiful herb garden right in the comfort of your own home. So, what are you waiting for? Get started on your own herb garden today!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Also, while you are at it, feel free to check out our blogs on&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-decor\/air-purifying-indoor-plants\/\">Air-Purifying Indoor Plants<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/kitchen-garden-ideas\/\">Kitchen Garden Expert Tips<\/a><\/li><\/ul>\n\r\n\r